data.title: Tasty and Satifying
data.text: Went here on a lunchtime and were comforted by the fact that they were busy.  We absolutely enjoyed our meal and were truly surprised by how small the bill was.  Service was prompt and efficient, place was clean and comfortable.

data.title: Food lacked flavor...
data.text: My daughters boyfriend wanted Chinese food and found this restaurant on Trip Advisor. Our family went for lunch on a Sunday afternoon. From the outside it looked really run down, but we decided to give it a try. The inside is very nice and clean. We were impressed. You can tell the ownership and staff care about the place. The waitstaff was VERY nice. From the moment we walked in the door, they were nice to us and very attentive. The only issue that we had was with the food itself. It was very bland and lacked flavor. We had egg rolls as an appetizer and they were good, but plain. I had sweet and sour chicken for my entree. The sauce was an orange color. It looked a bit strange. It wasn't horrible tasting, but it just didn't have any flavor. The rest of our meals were just lacking in flavor too. Unfortunately every one of us ended up sick to our stomachs. I gave it 2 stars because of the cleanliness and wonderful staff. We really wish the food was better. Probably will not come back.

data.title: Yum!
data.text: We ate here on a summer Sunday and we were the only people in the place other than the staff.  Great selection of Vietnamese dishes, well prepared.  The beef noodle soup was outstanding.  The roasted pork pho was very good, but a bit salty.  The beef pho was a disappointment because the quality of the beef was not so great.  Very fatty/grizzly.  Spring rolls were excellent.  I don't think their Sriracha is actually the original Huy Fong brand.  Didn't taste like the original to me, but still was ok.  Very good for cheap eats in a college town.

data.title: Great taste
data.text:
I love their pho noodles!!! The portion is fair to the price. For about $8 you get a large bowl of combination of noodles, some vegetables, several slices of beef, and approx. 2 meatballs(not sure, they sliced them into half). The soup is rich, but not greasy. 
The service was good, too.
I will revisit for sure.

data.title: We liked it
data.text: We stayed at the La Quinta and just walked over to Vy's. I had chicken fried rice. It was good. It needed soy sauce to liven up the flavors. A friend had salmon and said it was good and another friend had one of the Vermicelli bowls and it was very good. The wait staff was very good.

data.title: Bland
data.text: Ordered the Mongolian Beef, one friend had Pad Thai, another had Garlic Chicken. Never had Mongolian Beef with carrots and no spice. The Garlic Chicken had no garlic and the Pad Thai was Bad Thai......Just say NO

data.title: No  Reservation Big Party = Service Slow
data.text: After a high school graduation we went there to eat with 12 people.  They were out of many of the items we had chosen.  Three of our party order Chicken Curry (which is a lunch time staple).  Of the 12 were the last to be served so that was a bit disappointing.  The second disappointing thing was the spiciness of the curry - it was positively bland.  No one in the rest of the party had anything negative to say about their food so it must have been good or they would have said lots.  I would say the staff and the cook were overwhelmed by the size of our party.

data.title: Terrible Service
data.text: One diner decided to make a meal of two appetizers and another ordered a regular meal.  Despite being told that both should be served at the same time, the appetizers were delivered and then no meal for another 15 minutes, when we had to ask to be served.  That meal which showed up after the other diner was finished was the wrong order.  There are lots of places to get Asian food of average quality in College Station with much better service.

data.title: Do you love Asian fusion?  Then find somewhere else...
data.text:
Came down to College Station to visit our son and his fiance. Vy's was close to our hotel so we chose this place.

O.k, so it is super bowl Sunday, we pull up, no cars at all in the lot, but the open sign in on.  They were open, score one for the home team, or so we thought.

Seated promptly, 5 in our party, they brought out 4 waters, missed on that.  We got our menus, nice selection.   The waiter was really prompt off the bat, but it went downhill from there.  After about 10 minutes he came back, now remember at this time, there was 1 table with customers, ours.  Anyway, we order, all is well, or so we thought.  About 5 minutes later he comes back to tell us that the beef dinner my wife ordered could not be done as they were out, so order something else.  Our son and myself had ordered the beef with asparagus, he said no problem they had that, just not the grilled sliced beef.   Anyway, he comes back directly, oh, no sliced beef at all, so you need to order something different, so a complete miss on 3 of 5 orders off the bat.   Here is a hint for the owner.   Stock your menu items or get them off the menu, no sliced beef, no tempura shrimp, ......   should have left then.

During the time the place is starting to fill up.

About 5 minutes later we get 2 of 3 appetizers, the final one came after dinner got there.  Dinner service was a huge joke, 1 meal, the every 5 minutes the next would arrive.  Basically the service was perhaps the worst we had ever experienced. 

The dinners were overall very bland and tasteless, just a horrible experience.  You actually could probably get tastier food and better service at the corner gas station.

So with all that in mind I would recommend finding another Asian cuisine to hit up, or find a taco bell so you won't be disappointed. 

Now onto the overall experience.  The decor and design of the place is a tad schizophrenic, kind of like an interior designer walked in and exploded.  Very crazy. 

The food is presented looking very nice (just lacking taste, seasoning is your friend).  The portions are huge.  

If they could find a way to actually have service, and get some taste to the food this would be a great start.  Then hire someone with a vision on how an asian restaurant should look, you might have a great place.  The major issue though overall is the service sucks.  If I could give it a negative I would.   Big waste of money.

data.title: Terrible experience!
data.text:
Warning: Not a good place of vegetarians. 

We had an absolutely terrible experience! From getting the order wrong (serving non-vegetarian food when asked for veg) to getting the billing wrong, it was a complete and utter mess. And terrible service. We had to wait 30 min just to get the billing in order. The food was so-so in taste, nothing great. 

Never going back there ever again.

data.title: Good/Authentic but pricey
data.text: Service was very nice! Food was good. Cost was a bit much. ~$4 for 2 egg rolls. Maybe it's just inflation. I would recommend and I will eat here again though.

data.title: Good food at affordable price
data.text: Good Vietnamese food with huge portion at affordable price.  The restaurant has variety of menu:  Vietnamese, Chinese, steak.  I ate Vietnamese pho house special and rice plate with ground pork, both are excellent.

data.title: Pho bowl
data.text:
Their pho is very unique and tasty and unlike the usual pho we got from Que Hong in DFW area. They are very generous in portion. Price is very reasonable. Lots of choices to choose from either noodle or family style meal.
Restaurant is spacious, servers are attentive, and the place is clean.

data.title: Asian food lovers hidden treasure
data.text: This little restaurant is where my husband and I choose to dine for lunch or dinner when we crave Asian food.  It is prepared on order and absolutely fantastic. Huge servings and friendly staff.

data.title: WORST service in my life.
data.text:
I was one of the first people to come into the restaurant and sit down with my group. Our orders were taken after 20 minutes, people who came after were being served before us.

I ordered a house special, which NEVER CAME after even 1.5 HOURS. Simply put, I cancelled my order and left. I should've put in a word with the manager with the Spanish waiter who clearly didn't care for anything. 

It is the waiter's job to know the progress of the food, especially when it is coming very late. 

NEVER going to this restaurant again until new and better service is hired.

data.title: Slow, Bland, Strange, Overpriced
data.text:
Went here for dinner and had the shrimp with broccoli and egg drop soup.

Slow:  It was pretty empty when I arrived.  There is a host table, but no sign indicating whether you should wait to be seated, or seat yourself.  No staff were around.  After about a 5 minute wait alone, someone emerged and said I could sit where I pleased.  Refills of drinks were slow.  I even had to slurp on my straw and shake the ice in my cup (to no avail) to get the attention of someone for a refill.

Bland:  The egg drop soup was completely tasteless.  I had to add quite a bit of salt to get any taste, and I rarely add salt to any dish.

Strange:  The entrée had a strange flavor.  Afterwards I thought about how to describe it.  The best way to describe it was old coconut fried shrimp with the coconut dusted off, and mixed with old, recycled walnut-shrimp sauce.  It wasn't disgusting, but it was very palatable either.  The rice had a decent flavor, but the texture and consistency of it was less than desirable.

Overpriced.  Egg drop soup (small) was almost $4.  To be fair, it was pretty large.  Definitely not a cup - about the size of most soup bowls at other restaurants.  The entrees do not come with rice.  I asked for fried rice, assuming that was included in the entrée.  It is not.  All told, for the entrée, rice, soup (and water) cost just shy of $15.  For that amount I could have gotten a much more palatable meal elsewhere.  I should have just gone to Panda Express and paid less for better tasting food.

I won't be going back.

data.title: Good Food
data.text: I look forward to trying more dishes here.  I got take out today and the spring rolls were fantastic as was the Tom Yom Soup.  I can't wait to try the Vermicelli.

data.title: Best Spicy Noodle Soup Ever
data.text:
I travel around a lot but when i am home in College Station, i eat here weekly.
They have the best spicy noodle soup "House Special" that i have ever had! It is both delicate in flavor and all out spicy at the same time. I would recomend this to anyone who likes a good spicy soup!

data.title: Thanks but no Thanks
data.text: If you know what real Thai food place is supposed to taste like do not go here!  There were several other places to eat in the surrounding area and  am kicking myself for going here.  I got take out and the food didn't taste fresh, the Thai Tea wasn't good, the Pad Thai was just noodles and the spring rolls were not good for whoever said they were.  I'm headed to McDonalds!

data.title: Delicious Meal and Good Service
data.text: Spring Rolls were excellent.  Seafood soup also was excellent and a small bowl order would be more than enough for an average eater.  Recommend anyone to eat here especially if you like Asian Cuisine.  They also have other seafood on the menu that looked great
